HEAT RESISTANT: Put your safety first and mind at ease with our top-rated, superior quality silicone stove counter gap cover. Stove gap cover will not melt or be out of shape withstands up to 446℉ (230℃).

SIMPLE TO INSTALL: our stove gap covers have two sizes in 21 inches and 25 inches, which sit perfectly in place on all stovetops. Our stove gap covers are made of non-slip flexible silicone to fit around stoves and countertop and adapt to any uneven space. Easily customize to your stove by cutting to size using scissors
EASY TO CLEAN: The surface of stove gap cover is matte-brushed to resist stains and dust, and can be wiped down with just a damp cloth or cleaned in the dishwasher.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Can they be used if my stove and countertop are not the same height? Our carefully crafted design and flexible silicone material means that our gap covers conform to your gap, regardless if your stove and countertop are level. However, for a better and more snug fit, we recommend that the height difference is minimal. Do they melt on a stove and are they safe for my gas stove? Our premium silicone offers a high level of heat resistance, ensuring that they do not melt if used properly. Our design is such that there is a shorter flap which sits on the stove, with little exposure to any heat / flame produced by your hobs. Are they dishwasher safe? Absolutely! Simply stick them in the top rack of your dishwasher, and they’ll be good as new! Alternatively, you can simply wipe them down with a damp clothe. Can these be used for other appliances / uses around the house? Our gap covers can be used all across your home and the limits are endless. Wherever a gap exists in your home, our gap covers can come in handy. For example, a common use is to cover the gap between your washing machine & countertop or dryer. What size should I choose? It is important to measure your stove length before choosing your size. If the length is over 21inches but under 25 inches, simply opt for the 25 inch and cut to your desired size. We always recommend going for longer to avoid it being too short!
